main event: A half moon-shaped object, the size of a 25-cent piece, was observed by a MATS crew flying at an altitude of 20,000 feet at Biggs AFB, Texas.
interesting points: The object was observed moving from south to west.
The object was reported as a single white object.
The sighting was reported through an Air Force wire.
The case was evaluated as an astronomical object, specifically the planet Venus.
No further case file information was available.
sighted object: half moon-shaped object, size of 25 cent piece
